n  &lt;=<apex:outputText value="{0, number, ###,###,###,##0}"> <apex:param value="{!$Setup.ASI_MFM_Setting__c.ASI_MFM_KR_PO_Level1_Checking__c/10000000}" /> </apex:outputText>0M →  tolerance of  <apex:outputText value="{0, number, ###,###,###,##0}"> <apex:param value="{!$Setup.ASI_MFM_Setting__c.ASI_MFM_KR_PO_Level1_Amount__c/1000000}" /> </apex:outputText> M KRW<br/>★ For Plan  &gt; <apex:outputText value="{0, number, ###,###,###,##0}"> <apex:param value="{!$Setup.ASI_MFM_Setting__c.ASI_MFM_KR_PO_Level1_Checking__c/10000000}" /> </apex:outputText>0M →   tolerance of {!$Setup.ASI_MFM_Setting__c.ASI_MFM_KR_PO_Level2_Percent__c*100} % OR <apex:outputText value="{0, number, ###,###,###,##0}"> <apex:param value="{!$Setup.ASI_MFM_Setting__c.ASI_MFM_KR_PO_Level2_Amount__c/10000000}" /> </apex:outputText>0M KRW<br/></b><br/><br/>Hence additional PO cannot be created under above Plan #. <br/>Please create additional Plan and get approvals again if you want Purchasing team to issue PO under the Plan. <br/>Plan link : {!LEFT($Api.Partner_Server_URL_140, FIND('.com/',$Api.Partner_Server_URL_140)+3)}/{!RelatedTo.id}<br/>Thank you.<br/></messaging:htmlEmailBody></messaging:emailTemplate>